Titolo: Starcross (video game)

Anno: 1982

Descrizione: Starcross is a 1982 interactive fiction game written by Dave Lebling and published by Infocom. The game was released for the IBM PC (as a self-booting disk), Apple II, Atari 8-bit family, Commodore 64, TRS-80, Texas Instruments TI-99/4A, and later the Atari ST and Amiga. It was Infocom's fifth game and first in the science fiction genre. Starcross takes place in the year 2186, when the player's character is a lone black hole miner exploring an asteroid belt. It sold 90,315 copies.

Genere: Interactive fiction

Valutazione: N/A
